PART 2 — PLUGIN EXCEPTION
================================================================================

As a special exception, the copyright holder grants permission to link or
combine this program with independent plugin modules that communicate with
spectralQ exclusively through the documented Plugin API (the classes
BasePlugin, WatchZonePlugin, AIPlugin and the PluginManager interface defined
in the "plugins/" package), and to distribute the resulting combination under
terms of your choice, provided that:

1. You also meet, for each linked or combined independent plugin module, the
   terms and conditions of the license of that module.

2. Independent plugin modules that use the Plugin API are NOT considered
   derivative works of spectralQ Core and are NOT subject to the AGPL-3.0
   license, regardless of whether they are distributed as source code, compiled
   code, or as part of a larger application.

3. This exception does NOT apply to modifications of the spectralQ Core source
   code itself (files outside the "plugins/" directory). Any modifications to
   the core source code remain subject to the AGPL-3.0.

4. If you modify the Plugin API interfaces themselves, the modified interfaces
   and any code that depends on those modifications are subject to the AGPL-3.0.

This exception is granted to all recipients of spectralQ Core. It allows
third-party developers to create proprietary, commercial, or otherwise
independently licensed plugins without being required to release their plugin
source code under the AGPL-3.0.


